nge.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22pkafka%40insider.com%20(Peter%20Kafka)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A9%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftiktok-ban-app-american-us-not-worried-2024-9%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22China's%20growing%20aircraft%20carrier%20fleet%20is%20set%20to%20narrow%20the%20gap%20with%20the%20US%20Navy%20in%20carrier%20superiority%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223300%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22China's%20third%20aircraft%20carrier%2C%20the%20Fujian%2C%20docks%20in%20east%20China's%20Shanghai%20on%20April%2030%2C%202024.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6658e434d0b8e1c832ca7dfb%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222200%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EChina's%20third%20aircraft%20carrier%2C%20the%20Fujian%2C%20docks%20in%20east%20China's%20Shanghai%20on%20April%2030%2C%202024.%3Cp%3EPu%20Haiyang%2FXinhua%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20US%20Navy's%20aircraft%20carriers%20have%20long%20been%20regarded%20as%20a%20showcase%20of%20naval%20superiority.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EAs%20budget%20woes%20plague%20the%20US%20Navy%2C%20China's%20fleet%20has%20rapidly%20grown%20to%20the%20largest%20in%20the%20world.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20People's%20Liberation%20Army%20Navy's%20growing%20naval%20power%20comes%20amid%20heightened%20tensions%20with%20Taiwan.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EHistorically%2C%20the%20US%20aircraft%20carrier%20fleet%20has%20been%20a%20showcase%20of%20American%20military%20superiority.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20as%20the%20US%20Navy%20struggles%20to%20extend%20the%20lives%20of%20its%20oldest%20carriers%20to%20meet%20the%20nation's%20requirements%2C%20it%20maintains%20a%20fleet%20of%2011%20aircraft%20carriers%20%E2%80%94%20more%20than%20one-fifth%20of%20the%2047%20total%20in%20service%20worldwide.%20And%20that%20figure%20does%20not%20even%20count%20the%20smaller%20amphibious%20assault%20ships%20capable%20of%20holding%20squadrons'%20worth%20of%20aircraft%20and%20helicopters.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20amphibious%20assault%20ships%20dwarf%20the%20carriers%20of%20countries%20like%20Spain%2C%20Turkey%2C%20and%20South%20Korea.%20For%20American%20supercarriers%20in%20the%20legacy%20Nimitz%20and%20new%20Gerald%20R.%20Ford%20classes%2C%20there%20is%20no%20size%20equivalent%20anywhere%20in%20the%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYet%2C%20one%20country%20has%20designs%20on%20US%20carrier%20superiority%2C%20and%20size%20is%20not%20the%20only%20thing%20that%20matters%3A%20China%20has%20turned%20heads%20with%20its%20third%20and%20newest%20carrier%2C%20the%20Fujian%2C%20which%20set%20out%20on%20its%20maiden%20voyage%20in%20May.%20At%2080%2C000%20tons%20of%20displacement%2C%20this%20new%20carrier%20class%20is%20set%20to%20be%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.naval-technology.com%2Fnews%2Fanalysis-what-we-know-about-the-fujian-chinas-new-aircraft-carrier%2F%3Fcf-view%26cf-closed%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20largest%20in%20the%20world%20apart%20from%20the%20Nimitz%20and%20Ford%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20with%20room%20on%20the%20flight%20deck%20for%20up%20to%2060%20aircraft.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Fujian%20is%20formidable%20for%20other%20reasons%2C%20too.%20Like%20US%20carriers%2C%20it%20has%20a%20catapult-assisted%20takeoff%20but%20arrested%20recovery%20(CATOBAR)%20system%20that%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fchinapower.csis.org%2Fchina-type-003-fujian-aircraft-carrier%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egives%20it%20more%20plane-launching%20power%3C%2Fa%3E%20than%20the%20%26quot%3Bski%20jump%26quot%3B%20carriers%20used%20by%20the%20UK%20and%20other%20countries.%20The%20catapult%20uses%20electromagnetic%20power%20rather%20than%20steam%2C%20a%20cutting-edge%20technology%20that%20debuted%20with%20the%20Ford%20supercarrier%20class.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20vessel%2C%20however%2C%20runs%20on%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fchinapower.csis.org%2Fchina-type-003-fujian-aircraft-carrier%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Econventional%20rather%20than%20nuclear%3C%2Fa%3E%20power%2C%20setting%20it%20apart%20from%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20US%20carrier%20fleet%20and%20making%20its%20demand%20for%20fuel%20a%20potential%20liability.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20changes%20might%20seem%20small%2C%20but%20maritime%20observers%20call%20them%20significant.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhile%20China's%20older%20ski-jump%20carriers%20must%20rely%20on%20helicopters%20with%20small%2C%20rotating%20radars%20or%20land-based%20aircraft%20for%20airborne%20early%20warning%20and%20control%2C%20Fujian%3Cem%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3Ewill%20be%20able%20to%20launch%20larger%20AEW%26amp%3BC%20aircraft%20like%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sohu.com%2Fa%2F684916045_121118979%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EKJ-600%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20an%20aircraft%20similar%20to%20the%20US%20Navy's%20E-2D%20Hawkeye%2C%26quot%3B%20authors%20J.%20Michael%20Dahm%20and%20Peter%20W.%20Singer%20wrote%20for%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.defenseone.com%2Fideas%2F2024%2F06%2Fchinas-latest-aircraft-carrier-much-more-big-ship%2F397188%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EDefenseOne%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20June.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20ability%20to%20launch%20the%20KJ-600%20will%20revolutionize%20China's%20carrier%20operations%2C%20allowing%20the%20task%20group%20to%20operate%20independently%2C%20farther%20from%20Chinese%20territory%20with%20a%20powerful%20airborne%20radar%20high%20overhead%20offering%20comprehensive%20battlespace%20awareness%20for%20hours%20at%20a%20time%2C%26quot%3B%20they%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBryan%20McGrath%2C%20a%20retired%20Navy%20surface%20officer%20and%20managing%20director%20of%20the%20consulting%20firm%20The%20FerryBridge%20Group%2C%20told%20Sandboxx%20News%20that%20the%20smaller%20displacement%20of%20the%20new%20Chinese%20carrier%20compared%20to%20the%20US%20classes%20matters%20less%20to%20him%20than%20what%20the%20warship%20has%20on%20board.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMcGrath%20said%20he%20was%20impressed%20at%20China's%20adoption%20of%20electromagnetic%20launch%2C%20which%20allows%20for%20calibration%20of%20energy%20to%20launch%20a%20variety%20of%20platforms%20of%20different%20sizes%20and%20weights.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20they're%20catching%20on%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BThey're%20early%20adopters.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20noted%20that%20the%20ability%20of%20a%20carrier%20to%20launch%20and%20recover%20an%20airborne%20early%20warning%20aircraft%20like%20the%20E-2D%20%E2%80%94%20a%20hallmark%20of%20US%20carriers%2C%20but%20beyond%20the%20capability%20of%20American%20amphibious%20assault%20ships%20%E2%80%94%20%26quot%3Bgives%20us%20literally%20hundreds%20of%20miles%20of%20command%20and%20control%20around%20the%20aircraft%20carrier.%26quot%3B%20With%20the%20Fujian%20in%20the%20fleet%2C%20the%20Chinese%20will%20enjoy%20a%20similar%20advantage.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChina's%20first%20carrier%2C%20the%20Liaoning%2C%20also%20underwent%20a%20recent%20refurbishment%2C%20while%20a%20fourth%20carrier%20is%20believed%20to%20be%20under%20construction.%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faviationweek.com%2Fdefense-space%2Faircraft-propulsion%2Fchinese-carrier-aircraft-fleet-poised-rapid-growth%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESome%20observers%20think%20China%3C%2Fa%3E%20may%20have%20six%20carriers%20by%20the%202030s.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20US%20would%20still%20have%20nearly%20twice%20as%20many%20carriers%20as%20China%20if%20that%20prediction%20comes%20true%2C%20McGrath%20explained%20it%20would%20make%20for%20a%20different%20kind%20of%20presence%20and%20maritime%20competition.%20A%20four-carrier