20Jean-Louis%20became%20debt-free%20in%20two%20and%20a%20half%20years.%3Cp%3EJames%20Hill%20Photography%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3ELeo%20and%20Faith%20Jean-Louis%20were%20paying%20about%20%242%2C200%20in%20minimum%20monthly%20payments%20towards%20their%20debt.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EIt%20would%20have%20taken%20them%2015%20years%20and%20an%20additional%20%24125%2C000%20of%20interest%20to%20pay%20it%20off.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EInstead%2C%20they%20did%20it%20in%20two-and-a-half%20years%20by%20budgeting%20and%20working%20side%20hustles.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20summer%20of%202017%2C%20Leo%20Jean-Louis%2C%20an%20occupational%20therapist%2C%20and%20his%20now-wife%20Faith%20Jean-Louis%2C%20a%20pediatric%20nurse%20practitioner%2C%20got%20married%2C%20combining%20their%20debt%20for%20a%20total%20of%20%24211%2C000%20between%20their%20student%20loans%20and%20credit%20cards.%20That%20number%20gradually%20increased%20to%20%24224%2C000%20because%20of%20interest.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20order%20to%20maintain%20their%20debt%20payments%2C%20the%20couple%20had%20a%20minimum%20monthly%20payment%20of%20%242%2C200%20between%20the%20two%20of%20them.%20At%20that%20rate%2C%20it%20would%20take%20them%2015%20years%20and%20cost%20them%20%24125%2C000%20in%20additional%20interest%20to%20pay%20off%20their%20debt.%20They%20knew%20they%20couldn't%20feel%20fully%20free%20until%20they%20were%20able%20to%20get%20that%20out%20of%20the%20way.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20returning%20from%20their%20honeymoon%20in%20Greece%2C%20they%20decided%20to%20tackle%20their%20debt%20and%20pay%20it%20off%20as%20soon%20as%20possible.%20They%20didn't%20initially%20know%20how%20many%20years%20they%20could%20cut%20out.%20But%2C%20two-and-a-half%20years%20later%2C%20they%20found%20themselves%20debt-free.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20November%202019%2C%20they%20became%20debt-free%20aside%20from%20their%20mortgage.%20In%202020%2C%20they%20were%20able%20to%20reallocate%20their%20monthly%20payments%20and%20saved%20and%20invested%20%24127%2C000.%20They%20piled%20up%20%2446%2C000%20in%20savings%2C%20then%20put%20a%20total%20of%20%2481%2C000%20into%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Fbest-529-plans%5C%22%3E529%20account%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20their%20son's%20college%20tuition%2C%20their%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Fwhat-is-401k%5C%22%3E401(k)s%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20their%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Fwhat-is-roth-ira%5C%22%3ERoth%20IRAs%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20their%20combined%20Health%20Savings%20Account.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere's%20how%20they%20did%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EThey%20determined%20the%20'why'%20factor%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20started%20with%20our%20'why'%20because%20we%20knew%20we%20needed%20something%20more%20than%20a%20number%20to%20keep%20us%20motivated%20along%20our%20journey%2C%26quot%3B%20Leo%20told%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20so%20we%20started%20with%20an%20end%20in%20mind.%20Once%20our%20vision%20was%20clear%2C%20the%20choices%20and%20the%20decision%20became%20easier%20to%20pursue.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETheir%20main%20motivation%20was%20to%20be%20able%20to%20pass%20down%20generational%20wealth%20to%20their%20children.%20Leo%20and%20Faith%20didn't%20want%20their%20kids%20to%20start%20their%20lives%20off%20financially%20behind%20or%20in%20debt%20like%20they%20did.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20second%20reason%20was%20to%20achieve%20financial%20independence%2C%20which%20meant%20not%20being%20confined%20to%20a%20strict%2040-hours-a-week%20schedule%20and%20being%20able%20to%20travel%20and%20spend%20more%20time%20with%20their%20kids.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EThey%20figured%20out%20how%20much%20they%20owed%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFaith%20was%20still%20in%20school%20when%20the%20couple%20met%2C%20and%20hadn't%20looked%20at%20her%20debt%20numbers%20as%20a%20whole%3B%20Leo%20was%20familiar%20with%20how%20much%20he%20owed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20they%20married%2C%20they%20sat%20down%20and%20laid%20out%20Faith's%20various%20debts%20on%20an%20Excel%20sheet%20to%20find%20their%20overall%20debt%20number.%20Knowing%20what%20they%20were%20up%20against%20was%20a%20big%20part%20of%20understanding%20their%20endpoint.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EThey%20started%20budgeting%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20newlyweds%2C%20they%20didn't%20have%20a%20good%20sense%20of%20what%20their%20combined%20budget%20would%20look%20like.%20So%20they%20started%20talking%20about%20their%20bills%2C%20figuring%20out%20what%20they%20could%20cut%20out%20and%20what%20expenses%20could%20be%20combined.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20started%20packing%20their%20lunches%2C%20which%20saved%20them%20about%20%243%2C600%20a%20year.%20They%20carpooled%20to%20work%20on%20the%20days%20they%20were%20working%20on%20the%20same%20side%20of%20town%2C%20which%20saved%20them%20approximately%20%243%2C000%20a%20year.%20Cooking%20dinner%20at%20home%20became%20the%20new%20norm.%20And%2C%20since%20they%20were%20both%20busy%2C%20cutting%20cable%20was%20easy%2C%20which%20saved%20them%20approximately%20%24720%20a%20year.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20implemented%20the%20zero-sum%20budget%2C%20where%20they%20assigned%20a%20task%20to%20every%20dollar%20earned%2C%20and%20they%20used%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fbanking%2Fbest-budgeting-apps%5C%22%3Ebudgeting%20apps%3C%2Fa%3E%20Mint%20and%20Ramsey%20Every%20Dollar%20to%20track%20their%20cash.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20knew%20what%20our%20money%20was%20doing%20because%20we%20told%20it%20what%20to%20do%2C%26quot%3B%20Leo%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Caside%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENeed%20help%20with%20your%20money%3F%20Consider%20a%20financial%20advisor.%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsmartasset.com%2Fretirement%2Ffind-a-financial-planner%3Futm_source%3Dbusinessinsider%26utm_medium%3Dcpc%26utm_campaign%3Dbus__falc_bicontent%26utm_content%3DBI%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFinding%20a%20financial%20advisor%3C%2Fa%3E%20doesn't%20have%20to%20be%20hard.%20SmartAsset's%20free%20tool%20matches%20you%20with%20up%20to%20three%20fiduciary%20financial%20advisors%20who%20serve%20your%20area%20in%20minutes.%20Each%20advisor%20has%20been%20vetted%20by%20SmartAsset%20and%20is%20held%20to%20a%20fiduciary%20standard%20to%20act%20in%20your%20best%20interests.%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsmartasset.com%2Fretirement%2Ffind-a-financial-planner%3Futm_source%3Dbusinessinsider%26utm_medium%3Dcpc%26utm_campaign%3Dbus__falc_bicontent%26utm_content%3DBI%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20Start%20your%20search%20now.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Faside%3E%3Ch2%3EThey%20got%20side%20hustles%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20they%20ran%20out%20of%20things%20to%20cut%20from%20their%20budget%2C%20they%20turned%20their%20attention%20to%20income.%20Leo%20and%20Faith%20had%20five%20jobs%20between%20the%20two%20of%20them%20while%20they%20were%20trying%20to%20pay%20down%20their%20debt%20%E2%80%94%20their%20main%20jobs%20and%20three%20side%20hustles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20leveraged%20the%20skills%20they%20already%20had%20to%20take%20on%20additional%20jobs%3A%20Faith%20babysat%20and%20took%20overnight%20nursing%20shifts%2C%20while%20Leo%20picked%20up%20shifts%20at%20the%20hospital%20as%20an%20occupational%20therapist%20on%20weekends%20and%20holidays.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBetween%20the%20two%20of%20them%2C%20their%20first%20year%20of%20side%20hustles%20in%202018%20brought%20them%20an%20additional%20%2466%2C000.%20Their%20second%20year%20brought%20in%20%2440%2C000.%20They%20made%20sure%20it%20all%20went%20towards%20debt.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EThey%20paid%20their%20debt%20off%20in%20a%20certain%20order%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20tackle%20their%20debt%2C%20they%20started%20by%20paying%20those%20with%20the%20highest%20interest%20rates%20while%20making%20the%20minimum%20payments%20on%20all%20other%20debts%2C%20known%20as%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Fdebt-snowball-vs-debt-avalanche%5C%22%3Edebt%20avalanche%3C%2Fa%3E%20method.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Faith%20couldn't%20see%20the%20progress%20as%20quickly%20as%20she%20wanted%20to%2C%20so%20they%20eventually%20switched%20to%20the%20debt%20snowball%20method%2C%20where%20you%20pay%20the%20smallest%20debts%20first%20before%20moving%20to%20the%20next%20smallest%20amount%2C%20while%20paying%20the%20minimum%20on%20all%20others.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20snowball%20method%20became%20a%20major%20part%20of%20Faith%20buying%20into%20the%20process%20because%20she%20could%20see%20quicker%20results%20as%20the%20small%20loans%20were%20knocked%20out%20entirely.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSeeing%20those%20quick%20wins%20was%20a%20big%20psychological%20boost%20for%20her%2C%26quot%3B%20Leo%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20also%20kept%20a%20freedom%20meter%2C%20which%20was%20a%20giant%20poster%20thermometer%20where%20they%20would%20cross%20out%20each%20debt%20as%20it%20was%20paid%20off.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20was%20originally%20published%20in%20March%202021.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-couple-paid-off-debt-under-3-years-2024-9%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1725999362000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6041081ab46d720018b04dda%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-couple-paid-off-debt-under-3-years-2024-9%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22They%20realized%20why%20it%20was%20important%20to%20be%20debt-free%2C%20they%20figured%20out%20how%20much%20they%20owed%2C%20they%20kept%20a%20budget%2C%20and%20they%20worked%20a%20few%20side%20hustl