Cp%3EThe%20United%20Aarb%20Emirates%20or%20UAE%20has%20inked%20an%20agreement%20with%20India%20that%20provides%20a%20framework%20for%20giving%20services%20for%20operation%20and%20maintenance%20of%20nuclear%20power%20plants%20in%20the%20emirate.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Memorandum%20of%20Understanding%20was%20signed%20by%20Bhuwan%20Chandra%20Pathak%2C%20Chairman%20and%20Managing%20Director%20of%20the%20Nuclear%20Power%20Corporation%20of%20India%20Limited%20(NPCIL)%2C%20and%20Mohamed%20Al%20Hammadi%2C%20the%20Managing%20Director%20and%20Chief%20Executive%20Officer%20of%20the%20Emirates%20Nuclear%20Energy%20Corporation%20(ENEC)%20of%20the%20UAE.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20MoU%20was%20inked%20during%20the%20ongoing%20visit%20of%20Abu%20Dhabi%20Crown%20Prince%20Sheikh%20Khaled%20bin%20Mohamed%20bin%20Zayed%20Al%20Nahyan%20to%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Crown%20Prince%20held%20India-UAE%20bilateral%20discussions%20with%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20on%20Monday.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20MoU%20provides%20a%20general%20framework%20for%20the%20possible%20collaboration%20between%20the%20NPCIL%20%26amp%3B%20ENEC%20in%20the%20relevant%20fields%2C%20which%20inter%20alia%20include%20developing%20supply%20chains%2C%20sharing%20experience%20and%20providing%20services%20for%20Operation%20%26amp%3B%20Maintenance%20of%20Nuclear%20Energy%20Plants%2C%20providing%20nuclear%20consulting%20services%2C%20human%20resources%20development%20%26amp%3B%20training%2C%20research%20and%20development%20etc%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20statement%20by%20the%20NPCIL%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20NPCIL%20is%20a%20Public%20Sector%20Enterprise%20of%20the%20Department%20of%20Atomic%20Energy%20and%20operates%20all%20civil%20nuclear%20power%20plants%20in%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20ENEC%20is%20wholly%20owned%20by%20the%20Abu%20Dhabi%20Development%20Holding%20Company%20PJSC%2C%20which%20in%20turn%20is%20wholly%20owned%20by%20the%20government%20of%20the%20UAE.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20signing%20of%20this%20MoU%20marks%20a%20significant%20step%20in%20the%20growing%20cooperation%20between%20India%20and%20the%20UAE%20in%20peaceful%20uses%20of%20nuclear%20energy%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20NPCIL%20statement%20said%20today.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1725978660000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.ndtvimg.com%2Fi%2F2017-03%2Fnuclear-reactor-istock_650x400_51490779852.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fuae-inks-pact-for-india-to-operate-nuclear-power-plants-in-gulf-nation-6534555%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20United%20Aarb%20Emirates%20or%20UAE%20has%20inked%20an%20agreement%20with%20India%20that%20provides%20a%20framework%20for%20giving%20services%20for%20operation%20and%20maintenance%20of%20nuclear%20power%20plants%20in%20the%20emirate.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fuae-inks-pact-for-india-to-operate-nuclear-power-plants-in-gulf-nation-6534555%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Shashi%20Tharoor%20Gets%20Relief%20In%20Defamation%20Case%20For%20Remarks%20Against%20PM%20Modi%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20relief%20for%20Shashi%20Tharoor%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20on%20Tuesday%20stayed%20proceedings%20before%20a%20trial%20court%20in%20a%20defamation%20case%20lodged%20against%20the%20Congress%20MP%20for%20his%20alleged%20%26quot%3Bscorpion%20on%20Shivling%26quot%3B%20remarks%20targeting%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20bench%20of%20Justice%20Hrishikesh%20Roy%20and%20Justice%20R%20Mahadevan%20issued%20notice%20to%20the%20Delhi%20Police%20and%20BJP%20leader%20Rajiv%20Babbar%2C%20who%20is%20the%20complainant%20in%20the%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Tharoor%20was%20supposed%20to%20appear%20before%20a%20trial%20court%20here%20on%20Tuesday%20in%20pursuance%20of%20a%20Delhi%20high%20court%20order.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIssue%20notice%20returnable%20in%20four%20weeks.%20In%20the%20meantime%2C%20further%20proceedings%20in%20pursuance%20to%20the%20impugned%20judgement%20are%20stayed%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20bench%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Tharoor%20has%20moved%20the%20top%20court%20against%20the%20Delhi%20High%20Court%20order%20which%20refused%20to%20quash%20defamation%20proceedings%20against%20him%20on%20August%2029.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20hearing%2C%20advocate%20Mohammed%20Ali%20Khan%2C%20appearing%20for%20Mr%20Tharoor%2C%20submitted%20that%20the%20complainant%20cannot%20be%20said%20to%20be%20an%20aggrieved%20party%20in%20the%20case%20and%20members%20of%20political%20party%20also%20cannot%20be%20said%20to%20be%20an%20aggrieved%20party.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Khan%20added%20that%20Mr%20Tharoor's%20comment%20was%20protected%20under%20the%20immunity%20clause%20of%20the%20defamation%20law%2C%20which%20stipulates%20that%20any%20statement%20made%20in%20good%20faith%20was%20not%20criminal.%20He%20stated%20the%20High%20Court%20expanded%20the%20definition%20of%20%26quot%3Bperson%20aggrieved%26quot%3B%20in%20a%20defamation%20case%20to%20unacceptable%20limits.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20lawyer%20said%20Mr%20Tharoor%20made%20a%20reference%20to%20an%20article%20published%20in%20the%20Caravan%20magazine%20six%20years%20before%20the%20statement%20was%20made.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNone%20had%20any%20grievance%20to%20the%20article%20and%20the%20uttered%20sentence%20as%20published%20in%20the%20magazine.%20However%2C%20when%20Mr%20Tharoor%20made%20a%20reference%20to%20the%20same%20article%2C%20same%20was%20perceived%20as%20defamatory%20by%20the%20complainant%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20lawyer%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20top%20court%20expressed%20surprise%20that%2C%20in%202012%2C%20the%20statement%20was%20not%20defamatory%20when%20the%20article%20was%20originally%20published.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEventually%20it%20is%20a%20metaphor.%20I%20have%20tried%20to%20understand.%20It%20refers%20to%20the%20invincibility%20of%20the%20person%20referred%20to%20(Modi).%20I%20do%20not%20know%20why%20somebody%20has%20taken%20objection%20here%2C%26quot%3B%20Justice%20Roy%20remarked%20during%20the%20hearing.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20top%20court%20on%20Monday%20had%20agreed%20to%20consider%20listing%20Tharoor's%20plea%20against%20the%20high%20court%20order.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20high%20court%2C%20which%20on%20October%2016%2C%202020%2C%20stayed%20the%20criminal%20proceedings%20against%20the%20Congress%20MP%20from%20Thiruvananthapuram%20in%20the%20defamation%20complaint%2C%20vacated%20the%20interim%20order%20and%20directed%20the%20parties%20to%20appear%20before%20the%20trial%20court%20on%20September%2010.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20refusing%20to%20quash%20the%20proceedings%20against%20Tharoor%2C%20the%20high%20court%20had%20said%20prima%20facie%2C%20imputations%20like%20%26quot%3Bscorpion%20on%20Shivling%26quot%3B%20against%20the%20prime%20minister%20were%20%26quot%3Bdespicable%20and%20deplorable%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20had%20said%20prima%20facie%2C%20the%20remarks%20defamed%20the%20prime%20minister%2C%20the%20ruling%20BJP%20as%20well%20as%20its%20office-bearers%20and%20members.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDismissing%20Tharoor's%20petition%20seeking%20quashing%20of%20the%20defamation%20proceedings%20pending%20before%20a%20trial%20court%2C%20the%20high%20court%20had%20said%20there%20was%20sufficient%20material%20before%20the%20judicial%20magistrate%20for%20summoning%20him%20under%20section%20500%20(punishment%20for%20defamation)%20of%20the%20Indian%20Penal%20Code%20(IPC).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Congress%20leader%20had%20sought%20setting%20aside%20the%20trial%20court's%20April%2027%2C%202019%20order%20summoning%20him%20as%20an%20accused%20in%20the%20criminal%20defamation%20complaint%20filed%20by%20Rajiv%20Babbar%20as%20also%20the%20November%202%2C%202018%20complaint.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20criminal%20complaint%20was%20filed%20against%20Tharoor%20in%20the%20trial%20court%20by%20Babbar%2C%20who%20claimed%20that%20his%20religious%20sentiments%20were%20hurt%20by%20the%20Congress%20leader's%20statement.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20October%202018%2C%20Tharoor%20had%20claimed%20that%20an%20unnamed%20RSS%20leader%20had%20compared%20Modi%20to%20%26quot%3Ba%20scorpion%20sitting%20on%20a%20Shivling%26quot%3B.%20The%20Congress%20leader%20had%20said%20it%20was%20an%20%26quot%3Bextraordinarily%20striking%20metaphor%26quot%3B.%20PTI%20PKS%20NSD%20NSD%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1725978300000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-06%2F5ba5ep8o_shashi-tharoor-_625x300_01_June_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fscorpion-on-shivling-shashi-tharoor-gets-relief-in-defamation-case-for-remarks-against-pm-modi-6532382%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22In%20a%20relief%20for%20Shashi%20Tharoor%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20on%20Tuesday%20stayed%20proceedings%20before%20a%20trial%20court%20in%20a%20defamation%20case%20lodged%20against%20the%20Congress%20MP%20for%20his%20alleged%20%26quot%3Bscorpion%20on%20Shivling%26quot%3B%20remarks%20targeting%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fscorpion-on-shivling-shashi-tharoor-gets-relief-in-defamation-case-for-remarks-against-pm-modi-6532382%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22CCI%20clears%20proposed%20merger%20of%20Tata%20Motors%20Finance%20into%20Tata%20Capital%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22publi