n%3Cbr%3E%5CnBennu%20is%20a%20near-Earth%20asteroid%20that%20is%20being%20explored%20by%20NASA's%20OSIRIS-REx%20mission.%20OSIRIS-REx%20arrived%20on%20Bennu%20in%20Dec.%202018%20and%20expected%20to%20find%20a%20surface%20similar%20to%20a%20sandy%20beach.%20Expectations%20did%20not%20match%20reality.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5CnFull%20episode%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2FxH4Gz1RZJb%5C%22%3Ehttps%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2FxH4Gz1RZJb%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2FuUtLA2I6kf%5C%22%3Epic.twitter.com%2FuUtLA2I6kf%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%E2%80%94%20NASA%20Artemis%20(%40NASAArtemis)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FNASAArtemis%2Fstatus%2F1234320058865913856%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3EMarch%202%2C%202020%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAsteroid%20Bennu%2C%20discovered%20in%201999%2C%20currently%20poses%20the%20greatest%20risk%20of%20impacting%20our%20planet.%C2%A0Measuring%201%2C574ft%20in%20diameter%20and%20weighing%2067%20million%20tonnes%2C%20it's%20wider%20than%20the%20Empire%20State%20Building%20and%20200%20times%20heavier.%20NASA%20observations%20indicate%20a%201%20in%202%2C700%20chance%20of%20impact%20on%20September%2024%2C%202182.%20If%20Bennu%20collides%20with%20Earth%2C%20it%20would%20release%20energy%20equivalent%20to%201.4%20billion%20tonnes%20of%20TNT%2C%20surpassing%20the%20combined%20energy%20of%20all%20nuclear%20weapons%20ever%20detonated.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3E2.%202023%20DW%20-%20The%20Valentine's%20Day%20asteroid%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAsteroid%202023%20DW%20is%20predicted%20to%20have%20a%20significant%20chance%20of%20colliding%20with%20Earth%20on%20February%2014%2C%202046.%20With%20a%20diameter%20of%20166ft%20(50m)%2C%20it's%20comparable%20in%20size%20to%20the%20asteroid%20that%20caused%20the%20destructive%20Chelyabinsk%20event%20in%202013.%20Travelling%20at%2021.78%20km%2Fs%20relative%20to%20the%20sun%2C%20a%20potential%20impact%20could%20level%20an%20entire%20city.%20Initially%2C%20space%20agencies%20estimated%20a%20concerning%201%20in%20607%20chance%20of%20collision.%20However%2C%20recent%20observations%20have%20significantly%20reduced%20the%20risk.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3E3.%C2%A01950%20DA%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAsteroid%201950%20DA%2C%20measures%20a%20massive%204%2C265ft%20(1.3km)%20in%20diameter%20and%20weighs%2071%20million%20tonnes.%20Its%20massive%20size%20and%20potential%20impact%20make%20it%20the%20most%20significant%20threat%20to%20Earth%2C%20with%20a%20collision%20releasing%20energy%20equivalent%20to%20detonating%2075%20billion%20tons%20of%20TNT%2C%20capable%20of%20triggering%20a%20global%20catastrophe%20on%20the%20scale%20of%20the%20dinosaur%20extinction%20event.%20Currently%2C%20the%20asteroid%20has%20a%201%20in%2034%2C500%20chance%20of%20impacting%20Earth%20on%20March%2016%2C%202880.%20In%202032%2C%20it%20will%20safely%20pass%20within%206%2C959%2C357%20miles%20(112%2C000%2C000%20km).%20In%20preparation%20for%20potential%20future%20threats%2C%20NASA%20and%20ESA%20are%20already%20testing%20asteroid%20deflection%20methods%2C%20including%20high-speed%20satellite%20collisions%2C%20to%20push%20dangerous%20asteroids%20off%20course.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3E4.%202023%20TL4%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAsteroid%202023%20TL4%2C%20discovered%20last%20year%2C%20has%20been%20identified%20as%20a%20potentially%20civilisation-ending%20threat%20due%20to%20its%20massive%20size%20and%20weight.%20Measuring%201%2C083ft%20(0.33km)%20in%20diameter%20and%20weighing%2043%20million%20tonnes%2C%20this%20space%20rock%20could%20unleash%20a%20blast%20150%20times%20more%20powerful%20than%20the%20Tsar%20Bomba.%20Fortunately%2C%20scientists%20have%20estimated%20a%20relatively%20low%20collision%20risk%20of%201%20in%20181%2C000%20on%20October%2010%2C%202119%2C%20providing%20ample%20time%20for%20space%20agencies%20to%20take%20action.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3E5.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%C2%A0%3Cstrong%3E2007%20FT3%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAsteroid%202007%20FT3%20is%20classified%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Blost%20asteroid%26quot%3B%20since%20it%20was%20last%20observed%20in%202007.%20Despite%20the%20uncertainty%2C%20NASA%20estimates%20a%20low%20probability%20of%20impact%2C%20with%20a%201%20in%2010%20million%20chance%20(0.0000096%25)%20of%20striking%20Earth%20on%20March%203%2C%202030%2C%20and%20a%20slightly%20lower%20chance%20of%201%20in%2011.5%20million%20(0.0000087%25)%20on%20October%205%2C%202024.%20If%20an%20impact%20were%20to%20occur%20in%20either%20year%2C%20the%20asteroid's%20energy%20release%20would%20be%20equivalent%20to%202.6%20billion%20tons%20of%20TNT%2C%20potentially%20causing%20regional%20devastation%2C%20but%20unlikely%20to%20trigger%20a%20global%20catastrophe.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3E6.%201979%20XB%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAsteroid%201979%20XB%2C%20unseen%20for%20approximately%2040%20years%2C%20is%20another%20%26quot%3Blost%20asteroid%26quot%3B.%20Despite%20the%20uncertainty%2C%20scientists%20have%20estimated%20a%201%20in%201.8%20million%20chance%20(0.000055%25)%20of%20impact%20on%20December%2014%2C%202113%2C%20based%20on%20observations%20from%20its%20initial%20discovery%20on%20December%2011%2C%201979.%20If%201979%20XB%20were%20to%20collide%20with%20Earth%2C%20the%20impact%20would%20release%20an%20enormous%20amount%20of%20energy%2C%20equivalent%20to%20the%20detonation%20of%2030%20billion%20tons%20of%20TNT.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EAsteroids%20colliding%20with%20Earth%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAsteroid%20collisions%20with%20Earth%20are%20surprisingly%20common%2C%20with%20NASA%20estimating%2048.5%20tonnes%20of%20meteoric%20material%20entering%20our%20atmosphere%20daily.%20Most%20burn%20up%2C%20producing%20shooting%20stars.%20However%2C%20larger%20objects%20that%20pierce%20the%20atmosphere%20and%20impact%20Earth%20are%20rare.%C2%A0Just%20because%20asteroid%20collisions%20are%20unlikely%2C%20it%20does%20not%20mean%20they%20are%20impossible.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20mitigate%20this%20risk%2C%20NASA%20and%20the%20European%20Space%20Agency%20operate%20programs%20to%20identify%2C%20categorise%2C%20and%20track%20Near%20Earth%20Objects%20(NEOs).%20These%20initiatives%20help%20monitor%20potential%20threats%2C%20ensuring%20we're%20better%20prepared%20for%20an%20asteroid%20impact.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1725976140000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-07%2Fun15ft5k_asteroid-generic_625x300_06_July_24.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fscience%2F6-dangerous-asteroids-on-collision-course-with-earth-first-one-may-hit-in-october-6534117%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Asteroid%20Bennu%2C%20discovered%20in%201999%2C%20currently%20poses%20the%20greatest%20risk%20of%20impacting%20our%20planet.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fscience%2F6-dangerous-asteroids-on-collision-course-with-earth-first-one-may-hit-in-october-6534117%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22'Demented'%3A%20Donald%20Trump%20facing%20questions%20about%20age%2C%20capacity%20in%20debate%20with%20Harris%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1725975829000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-113232715%2Cimgsize-1362563.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2Fdemented-donald-trump-facing-questions-about-age-capacity-in-debate-with-harris%2Farticleshow%2F113232681.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F113232681.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3EAs%20Donald%20Trump%20and%20Kamala%20Harris%20take%20to%20the%20ABC%20News%20debate%20stage%20tonight%2C%20it%20will%20be%2078-year-old%20Donald%20Trump%20facing%20the%20question%20of%20age%20and%20senili